The paper deals with natural language text processing and visualization, which suggests it could belong to the categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). However, since the paper focuses on the automated generation of MindMaps from text, which involves semantic understanding and hierarchical visualization, the most likely categories are cs.CL and cs.IR. The paper also mentions the use of ontology, which is a common topic in cs.AI. The evaluation of the generated MindMaps involves human subjects, which could also suggest the category of cs.HC. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.HC, in that order.
